<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-10-31T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-10-31T13:00:00-05:00" n="446" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d446">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/6353:
                                    Telegram</note>
                                <head>
                                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Germany</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Morris</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                            State</gloss>
                                    </hi>
                                </head>
                                <opener>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                                        <placeName>
                                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-10-31T20:00:00+02:00">October 31, 1940—8 p.m.</date>
                                        <lb/> [Received October 31—6:02 p.m.]</dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p>4549. Rumors that Germany will mediate between Greece and Italy
                                    are without foundation according to the Greek Minister who
                                    believes that Greek-German diplomatic relations will be broken
                                    shortly and that action to that end will await the return of
                                    Ribbentrop whose arrival is expected today.</p>
                                <closer>
                                    <signed>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Morris</hi>
                                    </signed>
                                </closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>